Yeah, you heard me right.<br>
<br>
Go into inventory, leftclick a bag, and hold your left button down, then it floats on the cursor. Drop it in the keypad. <br>
<br>
The goodie then is that you dont have to open inventory anymore to put stuff in bags. Just goto keypad 3, (shift 3), rightclick the bag while holding your loot, the bag pops into window, and put the stuff directly into bag.<br>
<br>
My no 1 keypad is <br>
<br>
1 - DD<br>
2 - pet back off<br>
3 - pet guard here<br>
4 - pet report health (a must!!!)<br>
5 - pet follow me<br>
6 - pet attack<br>
<br>
As you can see, it all goes into pet control :-)<br>
<br>
Another tip, if you team with a tank, make an assist button : (In the social screen, you can add many commands to one button) : <br>
<br>
/pet back off<br>
/pet back off<br>
/assist &lt;name&gt;<br>
/assist &lt;name&gt;<br>
/pet attack<br>
<br>
As you can see, first 2 commands are twice. That is to make certain that pet heeds you and that you get the assist going.<br>
<br>
I hear that on higher lvls, its VERY important to do the assist right, else the pet will hit wrong mob, and the enchanter will be ANGRY at you :-)<br>
